result.execSummary:
The defendant Lashaunte S Riley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Carrying Concealed Weapon. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Lashaunte S Riley in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Jessica Bellows appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for plea and sentencing.

Pursuant to plea negotitions and on motion of the state, Court ordered charge AMENDED to a County Ordinance #63.015, Carrying Concealed Weapons to which defendant plead guilty.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered defendant to pay a forfeiture of $250.00 including costs and surcharges by 6/13/2016. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
Defendant Lashaunte S Riley in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 12, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Lashaunte S Riley in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defense received discovery.  Status conference scheduled for February 15, 2016 at 08:30 am.

No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.
